## A.5 Business Requirements (BRD §5)

- **5.1 Centralized Data Management** — Single system for studies, sites, subjects, documents, tasks, and finances; eliminate spreadsheets and disconnected tools.
- **5.2 Workflow Automation** — Automate study, site, subject, and visit lifecycles; event-based task creation, reminders, and escalations; SLA enforcement with minimal manual intervention.
- **5.3 Configuration-Driven Flexibility** — Ability to configure protocols, visit schedules, and document requirements; no code changes for amendments.
- **5.4 Real-Time Visibility & Tracking** — Dashboards for study, site, and portfolio status; real-time tracking of tasks, visits, and milestones; alerts for delays, risks, and overdue activities.
- **5.5 Compliance & Auditability** — Complete audit trails for all actions and changes; role-based access control and data security; inspection-ready data and reports.
- **5.6 Subject & Visit Management** — Protocol-based visit scheduling with version control; automatic tracking of completed, missed, and overdue visits.
- **5.7 Document Management** — Centralized document repository with versioning; mandatory document checklists and approval workflows; easy retrieval for audits.
- **5.8 Financial Management** — Rule-based payments linked to visits and activities; budget tracking and version control; automated payment holds/releases.
- **5.9 Monitoring & Oversight** — CRA assignment and visit scheduling; monitoring reports tracking and follow-ups; automated milestone calculations (FPI, LPI, DBL).
- **5.10 Patient Engagement (Portal)** — Secure patient access to visits, tasks, and notifications; ability to update details and upload documents; automated reminders to reduce missed visits.
- **5.11 Scalability & Performance** — Support multiple studies, regions, and users simultaneously; maintain performance as trial complexity grows.
- **5.12 Deterministic & Validation-Friendly Design** — Rule-based (non-AI) decision-making; clear traceability of system behavior; easy validation and regulatory approval.

