## Epic 2: Site Management

### Story 01 – Register a New Site

**User Story:** As a Study Manager, I want to register new study sites so that they can participate in the clinical study.
**Detailed Description:** User must be able to enter site metadata including site name, code, location details, PI details, contact information, feasibility status, and regulatory information. System validates mandatory fields and ensures site code uniqueness.
**Acceptance Criteria:**

1. User can open "Register Site" form.
2. System enforces mandatory field validation.
3. Duplicate site codes are blocked.
4. Newly registered site defaults to "Pending Activation."
5. Site appears under the correct study.
6. Audit trail captures creation details.
**Size:** 5 (medium) | **Priority:** High

### Story 02 – Track Site Activation Status

**User Story:** As a Study Manager, I want to track the activation progress of each site so that I can monitor readiness for subject enrollment.
**Detailed Description:** System displays activation prerequisites such as feasibility completion, IRB/EC approval, contract completion, essential documents submission, and site initiation visit. Each milestone has a date and status.
**Acceptance Criteria:**

1. Activation dashboard displays all prerequisites.
2. Completed items shown as green; pending as red.
3. Site status switches automatically to "Active" once all prerequisites are met.
4. System records activation date.
5. Notifications sent to CRA and Study Manager.
**Size:** 8 (large) | **Priority:** High

### Story 03 – Enforce Activation Prerequisites

**User Story:** As a Study Manager, I want the system to enforce activation prerequisites so that sites cannot activate without required approvals and documents.
**Detailed Description:** System prevents activation if any required document or milestone is missing. System must list missing items and provide links to complete them.
**Acceptance Criteria:**

1. Activation blocked if any required item is incomplete.
2. Blocking message displays missing prerequisites clearly.
3. After completing prerequisites, system reevaluates status.
4. Activation attempt logged in audit trail.
**Size:** 8 (large) | **Priority:** High

### Story 04 – View Site Information

**User Story:** As a User, I want to view site information so that I can understand site status and operational progress.
**Detailed Description:** Displays full site details: metadata, activation timeline, documents, visit history, enrollment metrics, CRA assignments, monitoring visits, and contact details.
**Acceptance Criteria:**

1. Site overview page loads with all required data.
