### Story 02 – Budget Tracking (Planned vs Actual)

**User Story:** As a Finance Manager, I want to track budgets so that I can monitor study financial health and control overspending.
**Detailed Description:** System must show planned budget vs actual expenditure across categories such as investigator fees, monitoring, site payments, labs, and other cost buckets. Dashboard should highlight variances and allow drill-down into cost drivers.
**Acceptance Criteria:**

1. Budget overview displays planned vs actual amounts.
2. Variance is automatically calculated.
3. Filtering available by study, site, period, cost category.
4. Trend graphs show spending over time.
